      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is completely understandable why you feel this way, as emotional depletion can sometimes feel like a permanent state rather than a temporary phase. When the core of who you thought you were seems to have vanished, it feels profoundly like a loss. This deep sense of identity erosion needs careful exploration, which is why connecting with someone skilled in existential or deeper psychological work might be beneficial. Remember that even if the old self is diminished, it doesn't mean there is nothing left to build upon.",
      "source": "target",
