      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That image of the burnt-out house powerfully illustrates the depth of your current despair, and it is natural to feel hopeless when looking at such wreckage. Rather than thinking of rebuilding the old structure, perhaps the focus could be on tending to the ground itself—nurturing something new from the existing soil. Even when things feel utterly ashes, there is always the possibility of learning, caring for yourself, and finding a quiet, new presence beneath the surface. Seeking professional support to help you feel seen in this emptiness is a gentle continuation of self-care.",
